article.headline: Valparaiso 81, Toledo 49
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Brandon McPherson and Cory Johnson scored 15 points each to lead Valparaiso to a 81-49 victory against Toledo on Saturday. Johnson added nine rebounds, and Brandon Wood had 13 points for the Crusaders (4-6), who bounced back after consecutive losses against ranked schools Butler and Purdue. Jordan Dressler and Malcolm Griffin had nine points apiece for Toledo (3-8). The Rockets, whose only lead was 2-0, shot 37 percent (17 of 46) from the floor and had 18 turnovers.
